<span class="medium">
<h2>LIMS Developer's Manual - Inspecting Perl Warnings<br>
</h2>
<h3><span style="font-weight: bold;">Overview</span></h3>
<ul>
  <li>Perl warnings are shown if the Perl interpreter is run with the
-w switch.</li>
  <li>Since other bioinformatics users are replying on the LIMS
modules, it is good if we can get rid of most if not all Perl warnings
from our code.</li>
  <li>The bin/get_warnings.pl script will report Perl warnings
generated from our modules with suggested fixes.<br>
  </li>
</ul>
<h3>Details</h3>
<ul>
  <li>By default the script reports warnings from all our modules.<br>
  </li>
  <li>Different versions of Perl interpreter generates different
warnings.&nbsp; User can specify a particular Perl interpreter to be
used by the -i switch.</li>
  <li>User can specify a specific list of modules to inspect by the -m
switch.</li>
  <li>Use the -h switch to get help information.<br>
  </li>
</ul>
</span>
